<p>Is <code>char c2=i1&lt;&lt;8&gt;&gt;24;</code> valid C syntax? (Where <code>i1</code> is and unsigned integer) Additionally, will it yield the result of shifting <code>i1</code> 8 bits left and 24 bits right respectively? I am unpacking a char previously stored in <code>i1</code>, along with three other chars.  Code below:</p>  <pre><code>unsigned char b3 = 202; unsigned char b2 = 254; unsigned char b1 = 186; unsigned char b0 = 190; ...   unsigned int i1=202; i1=i1&lt;&lt;8; i1=i1+254; i1=i1&lt;&lt;8; i1=i1+186; i1=i1&lt;&lt;8; i1=i1+190; ...  char c1=i1&gt;&gt;24; char c2=i1&lt;&lt;8&gt;&gt;24; </code></pre>